                                                                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="15095496" author="kohlisankalp" created="Wed, 13 Jan 2016 02:35:28 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;cc &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=brandon.williams&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;brandon.williams&quot;&gt;brandon.williams&lt;/a&gt; Can you please review this?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15096588" author="brandon.williams" created="Wed, 13 Jan 2016 17:15:37 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Giving review to Jake since he handled the original patch.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15096750" author="tjake" created="Wed, 13 Jan 2016 18:40:17 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I don&apos;t see how this can work.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;If you have node A bootstrap and node B bootstrap at the same time, the ownership can not be strict since the ownership isn&apos;t stable. Overlapping ranges would be likely be pulled by both nodes (assuming vnodes). We would need something like &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CASSANDRA-9667&quot; title=&quot;strongly consistent membership and ownership&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;CASSANDRA-9667&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;CASSANDRA-9667&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; todo this.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15097169" author="kohlisankalp" created="Wed, 13 Jan 2016 22:36:52 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;If you have a large cluster and you are bootstrapping machines far apart in the ring, it will have no issues. Also we don&apos;t use vnodes. &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CASSANDRA-9667&quot; title=&quot;strongly consistent membership and ownership&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;CASSANDRA-9667&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;CASSANDRA-9667&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; will be in fixed in 3.x timeframe and we need to properly co-ordinate the moves/boostraps via tooling till we are on 3.x. &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15097173" author="kohlisankalp" created="Wed, 13 Jan 2016 22:39:03 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I am not changing the current behavior here...If you need simultaneous moves and bootstraps and make then far enough in the ring though tooling, this flag will let you do that. &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15097448" author="tjake" created="Thu, 14 Jan 2016 01:57:03 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt; we should only allow this if your aren&apos;t using vnodes then. can you add that logic?  &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15097455" author="kohlisankalp" created="Thu, 14 Jan 2016 02:11:21 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Sure I can add that. &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15097459" author="kohlisankalp" created="Thu, 14 Jan 2016 02:17:41 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Do you know the best way to check if it is running with vnodes? Just check if initial_token is null? &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15097491" author="tjake" created="Thu, 14 Jan 2016 02:48:06 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;yeah, 1 initial token or num_tokens: 1&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15097497" author="kohlisankalp" created="Thu, 14 Jan 2016 02:55:17 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;New patches attached&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15098264" author="tjake" created="Thu, 14 Jan 2016 15:42:16 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;pushed patch to a branch and kicked off &lt;a href=&quot;http://cassci.datastax.com/view/Dev/view/tjake/job/tjake-11005-dtest/&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;dtests&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=&quot;http://cassci.datastax.com/view/Dev/view/tjake/job/tjake-11005-testall/&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;utests&lt;/a&gt; will commit once it looks clean&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15101854" author="tjake" created="Fri, 15 Jan 2016 14:49:05 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;committed&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
